<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN237-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. veḷimāṉuḻaicceṉṟārkku avaṉaṟuñca iḷaveḷimāṉciṟitukoṭuppak koḷḷātu peruñcittiraṉār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN237">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>nīṭuvāḻ keṉṟiyā ṉeṭuṅkaṭai kuṟukip</l>
<l>pāṭi niṉṟa pacināṭ kaṇṇē</l>
<l>kōṭaik kālattuk koḻuniḻa lākip</l>
<l>poytta laṟiyā vuravōṉ cevimutal</l>
<l>vittiya paṉuval viḷaintaṉṟu naṉṟeṉa</l>
<l>nacci yirunta nacaipaḻu tāka</l>
<l>vaṭṭa kuḻici yaḻaṟpayan tāaṅ</l>
<l>kaḷiyar tāmē yārka veṉṉā</l>
<l>vaṟaṉil kūṟṟan tiṟaṉiṉṟu tuṇiya</l>
<l>vūḻi ṉuruppa verukkiya makaḷir</l>
<l>vāḻai pūviṉ vaḷaimuṟi citaṟa</l>
<l>mutuvā yokkaṟ paricila riraṅkak</l>
<l>kaḷḷi pōkiya kaḷariyam paṟantalai</l>
<l>veḷvēl viṭalai ceṉṟumāyn taṉaṉē</l>
<l>yāṅkatu nōyiṉ ṟāka vōṅkuvaraip</l>
<l>pulipārt toṟṟiya kaḷiṟṟirai piḻaippi</l>
<l>ṉelipārt toṟṟā tāku malitiraik</l>
<l>kaṭaṉmaṇṭu puṉali ṉiḻumeṉac ceṉṟu</l>
<l>naṉiyuṭaip pariciṟ ṟaruka</l>
<l>meḻumati neñcē tuṇipumun tuṟuttē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="2">On a day of hunger when I stood singing, </l>
<l corresp="1">having approached the tall gate saying “may he live long”, </l>
<l corresp="6a">longing that, </l>
<l corresp="3">there being fat shade in the time of the west wind, </l>
<l>the composition sown into the ear of a strong man</l>
<l>who does not know of lying will well bear fruit, (4f.)</l>
<l corresp="6b-d">  since the longing that existed was false, </l>
<l corresp="7">as if the pot that cooked yielded [only] fire, </l>
<l corresp="9">since virtuless Death today decided the matter, </l>
<l corresp="8">not saying “pitiable they are. Let them eat.” </l>
<l corresp="10">while women that are burningly harrasses in turn </l>
<l corresp="11">scatter broken pieces of bangles, like plantain flowers, </l>
<l corresp="12">While mendicants with [their] old-mouthed kinfolk are in grief, </l>
<l corresp="14">the warrior with a white spear has gone [and] vanished </l>
<l corresp="13">in the wasteland with saline soil where spurges have grown long. </l>
<l>While that thus is without pain, if a tiger on the high mountain</l>
<l>fails [to have as its] prey the elephant bull which  it hasve peered out at [and] attacked, (15f.)</l>
<l corresp="17a-c">it will not peer at [and] attack a rat. </l>
<l corresp="17d-18">Going sweetly like the flood that rushes in the sea with amply waves </l>
<l corresp="19">we will bring ample(?) gifts. </l>
<l>Rise, o heart, putting you resolve first.  </l>
</lg>
